'''Argentine Sign Language''' (Spanish: ''Lengua de señas argentina''; '''LSA''') is used in [[Argentina]]. Deaf people attend separate schools, and use local [[sign language]]s out of class. A manual alphabet for spelling [[Spanish language|Spanish]] has been developed.

