This article is a list of  '''[[national symbol]]s of the [[Confederate States of America|Confederate States]]''' enacted through [[legislation]]. Upon its [[independence]] (adoption of the [[Provisional Confederate States Constitution|Constitution for the Provisional Government of the Confederate States]]) on February 8, 1861,<ref>{{cite book |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |editor-last=Matthews |editor-first=James M. |date=1864 |title=The Statutes at Large of the Provisional Government of the Confederate States of America : From the Institution of the Government, February 8, 1861, to its Termination, February 18, 1862, Inclusive; Arranged in Chronological Order, Together with the Constitution for the Provisional Government, and the Permanent Constitution of the Confederate States, and the Treaties Concluded by the Confederate States with Indian Tribes |url=https://archive.org/stream/statutesatlarge00conf#page/8/mode/2up/search/%22Eighth+day+of+February%22 |location=Richmond |publisher=R. M. Smith, Printer to Congress |page=8 |ol=25389078M}}</ref> and subsequent [[Confederate States Constitution|foundation]] of the "permanent" government on February 22, 1862,<ref>{{cite book |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=Programme for the Inauguration of the President and Vice-President of the Confederate States |url=https://archive.org/details/programmeforinau00conf |date=1862 |ol=24601341M}}</ref> the [[Congress of the Confederate States|Confederate States Congress]] adopted national symbols distinct from those of the [[United States]].

