{{unreferenced|date=January 2013}}
[[Image:Osten.jpg|200px|right]]
'''Osten Transporter Bridge''' is an {{convert|80|m|0|adj=on}} long [[transporter bridge]] over the [[Oste]] River in [[Osten (Oste)]], [[Lower Saxony]], [[Germany]]. It was built in 1908-9 and was in regular use until 1974 and is now only used as a tourist attraction.
The bridge can transport 6 cars or 100 persons simultaneously.

