A '''sewing gauge''' is a [[ruler]], typically 6&nbsp;inches long, used for measuring short spaces. A space no longer than 6 inches in diameter. It is used to mark [[hem]]s for [[Tailoring|alterations]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=WiY0AAAAIBAJ&sjid=2uAIAAAAIBAJ&pg=5517,5450862 |publisher=[[Google Books]] |work=[[Bangor Daily News]] |date=Sep 15, 1971 |accessdate=2013-05-08 |title=6" Sewing Gauge Has New Easy-read-seam Double Point Slider}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://missourifamilies.org/learningopps/learnmaterial/tools/gauge.htm |title=Sewing Gauge-Sewing and Design Tools Dictionary |work=Missourifamilies.org |publisher=[[University of Missouri]] |date= |accessdate=2013-05-08}}</ref>

